/*
 * I2C_Scanner.ino — Automato Brain Board V2.0
 *
 * Generic I2C bus scanner with comprehensive device database.
 * Scans all 127 possible I2C addresses and identifies any device
 * found using a database sourced from https://i2cdevices.org
 * (MIT License — database auto-generated by i2cdevices.org)
 *
 * Brain Board I2C pins: SDA = IO6, SCL = IO7
 *
 * HOW TO USE:
 *   1. Flash to Brain Board with any Qwiic devices connected
 *   2. Open Serial Monitor at 115200 baud
 *   3. Press RESET to scan
 *   4. All found devices printed with part number and description
 *
 * Multiple matches at the same address are normal — many devices
 * share addresses. Use context to identify which one you have.
 *
 * DATABASE SOURCE: https://i2cdevices.org (updated 2026-03-17)
 * To refresh: download https://i2cdevices.org/devices.json
 */

